CBOverviewHelp

"<html>
<head>
<title> Overview of Code Crusader </title>
</head>

Code Crusader provides a complete UNIX development environment.
Its major features are:

<ul>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CBEditorHelp>Text editor</a>
     with <a href=jxhelp:CBCompleterHelp>keyword completion</a>,
     <a href=jxhelp:CBMacroHelp>macros</a>,
     and <a href=jxhelp:CBStylerHelp>context sensitive highlighting</a>
     for C/C++ and HTML
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CBProjectHelp>Project interface to UNIX <tt>make</tt></a>
<p>
<li> Ability to <a href=jxhelp:CBTasksHelp>run the finished program</a>
     from within Code Crusader
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CBTasksHelp>Interface</a> to
     <a href=http://www.newplanetsoftware.com/medic/>Code Medic</a>
     for debugging
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CBCTreeHelp>C++ class inheritance tree</a>
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CBJavaTreeHelp>Java class inheritance tree</a>
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CBManPageHelp>Interface to UNIX man pages</a>
     for information about system functions
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CBDiffHelp>Interface to UNIX diff</a>
     for displaying the differences between files
</ul>

For more information about a particular feature, simply click on the underlined text.
To search for a word or phrase, select \"Find...\" from the Search menu, enter the
text, and then select \"Search all sections\" from the Search menu.
<p>
If you are new to Code Crusader, please note that it faithfully
implements the Macintosh paradigm of allowing you to safely explore features
by always providing the ability to undo the result.

</html>"
